subject: p13031876
History: Status post extubation interval study. CHEST, SINGLE AP PORTABLE VIEW. Rotated positioning. NG type tube is present, tip beneath diaphragm, off film. A right subclavian central line is present, tip over distal SVC. Upper zone redistribution and pulmonary vascular plethora, consistent with CHF. Again seen is increased retrocardiac density consistent with left lower lobe collapse and/or consolidation. There is minimal atelectasis at the right base. Small bilateral effusions cannot be excluded. Incidental note is made of soft tissue anchors in the right humeral head and fusion hardware in the lower cervical spine.
Impression: Left lower lobe collapse and/or consolidation and CHF with possible small bilateral effusions, similar to at 3:56 am.
